According to a report by Intel Market Research, the Global Capability Center (GCC) as a Service Market was valued at USD 1.61 billion in 2025 and is projected to reach USD 2.62 billion by 2034, expanding at a CAGR of 7.3% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing steady growth as multinational enterprises increasingly adopt subscription-based GCC models to reduce capital expenditure, accelerate global expansion, and improve operational efficiency. By offering scalable services such as IT research and development, finance and accounting, customer support, human resources, analytics, procurement, engineering, and shared business services, GCC as a Service enables organizations to focus on innovation and strategic growth while leveraging globally distributed talent and technology infrastructure.
